Unilever Capital Corp NV is issuing a 65mln New Zealand dlr eurobond due July 7, 1989 with an 18-1/4pct coupon and priced at 101-1/4, bookrunner Hambros Bank Ltdsaid.    Joint lead managers are EBC Amro Bank Ltd and Hambros.  Thebonds, guaranteed by Unilever Plc, will be issued indenominations of 1,000 and 5,000 dlrs and listed in Luxembourg.    Fees comprise 1/2 pct for management and underwritingcombined and 7/8 pct for selling. REUTER&#3;